page.title: 09Park Wood, Harrold
page.content: Park Wood is a deciduous woodland covering 63.0 hectares of land. It is owned by a gentleman who lives in Northampton. The wood has lovely open rides, which add to it's floristic value. The trees are mainly Oak and Ash with some Birch and Sycamore and a little Aspen. There is a great deal of dead Elm which has resulted in an open canopy and made the general condition of the wood poor. Part of the wood has recently been cleared by the new owner and has been replanted. There is no evidence of the wood being used for game.
